Crunch
Wordlist generator with specific criteria

Password Attacks
Description
Crunch is a wordlist generator where you can specify a standard character set or a custom one. It can generate all possible combinations.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which crunch
Install command:

sudo apt install crunch
Basic Syntax
crunch <min> <max> [charset] -o <output>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
crunch 6 6 0123456789 -o pins.txt

6-digit PINs	Generate PIN list	
crunch 8 8 abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz -o words.txt

8-char lowercase	Simple passwords	
crunch 4 8 -t pass@@@@ -o wordlist.txt

Pattern: pass + 4 chars	Known prefix	
crunch 6 6 -t @@19@@ -o years.txt

Pattern with 19	Year patterns	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Determine password criteria
2
Select character set
3
Set min/max length
4
Use patterns if known
5
Generate wordlist
Understanding the Output
Creates wordlist file with all possible combinations.

Important Warnings
•
Large character sets create huge files
•
Disk space needed
•
Use patterns to reduce size
